1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,470
In this exercise, you are asked to recommend how you would set

2
00:00:04,470 --> 00:00:08,805
up the Scrum framework for the socialkare.com product delivery team.

3
00:00:08,805 --> 00:00:12,630
You were asked to include the core roles to be filled,

4
00:00:12,630 --> 00:00:15,480
the Scrum ceremonies to be conducted,

5
00:00:15,480 --> 00:00:20,535
and finally, the schedule and duration of the ceremonies as well as their agenda.

6
00:00:20,535 --> 00:00:22,860
Here are my responses.

7
00:00:22,860 --> 00:00:27,874
The three core roles in a Scrum framework are the are PO,

8
00:00:27,874 --> 00:00:31,540
Scrum Master and Agile Team.

9
00:00:31,540 --> 00:00:34,065
Let's start with a Scrum master role.

10
00:00:34,065 --> 00:00:38,180
This role is responsible for facilitating the Agile Team's work,

11
00:00:38,180 --> 00:00:40,280
obtaining resources for it,

12
00:00:40,280 --> 00:00:42,910
and protecting it from problems.

13
00:00:42,910 --> 00:00:47,235
The Scrum Master is servant leader to the PO and Agile Team.

14
00:00:47,235 --> 00:00:50,825
The next core role in Scrum is the Product Owner.

15
00:00:50,825 --> 00:00:54,050
The Product Owner represents the SocialKare.gov

16
00:00:54,050 --> 00:00:58,420
stakeholders and specifically is known as the voice of the customer.

17
00:00:58,420 --> 00:01:01,430
This is the one individual who's responsible for

18
00:01:01,430 --> 00:01:05,300
the prioritize work item list called a product backlog.

19
00:01:05,300 --> 00:01:10,190
This role is SocialKare.gov will be responsible for prioritizing the backlog,

20
00:01:10,190 --> 00:01:13,280
share business decisions in a timely manner,

21
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:16,460
and is responsible for providing any requirements or

22
00:01:16,460 --> 00:01:21,710
functionality related information to the Agile Team in a timely manner.

23
00:01:21,710 --> 00:01:26,330
The next core role in Scrum is the Agile Team member.

24
00:01:26,330 --> 00:01:31,400
Agile Team members are responsible for the creation and delivery of a system.

25
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:35,260
This role at SocialKare.gov will primarily include developers.

26
00:01:35,260 --> 00:01:40,370
However, all other Agile Team members will also be included in this category.

27
00:01:40,370 --> 00:01:43,220
This includes, but is not limited to,

28
00:01:43,220 --> 00:01:47,375
those who will conduct modeling, programming,

29
00:01:47,375 --> 00:01:52,625
testing, front-end design, business analysis,

30
00:01:52,625 --> 00:01:56,090
release activities, and others.

31
00:01:56,090 --> 00:01:59,630
In the retrospective, there's an opportunity for

32
00:01:59,630 --> 00:02:04,280
the Scrum team to inspect itself and create a plan for improvements.

33
00:02:04,280 --> 00:02:07,490
Team member discuss what went well during this sprint,

34
00:02:07,490 --> 00:02:10,160
as well as opportunities for improvement.

35
00:02:10,160 --> 00:02:16,310
This occurs once per sprint and is time-boxed to three hours per sprint.

36
00:02:16,310 --> 00:02:18,800
In the project vision ceremony,

37
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:21,980
the business articulates a business need that is intended to

38
00:02:21,980 --> 00:02:25,370
be achieved where they discuss the goals,

39
00:02:25,370 --> 00:02:27,125
who the sponsor is,

40
00:02:27,125 --> 00:02:28,960
what the vision is,

41
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:34,325
they clearly identify the success criteria as well as the assumptions and risks.

42
00:02:34,325 --> 00:02:40,205
The project vision ceremony occurs once per project and is time-boxed to one hour.

43
00:02:40,205 --> 00:02:45,230
In release planning, the organization develops a release plan that

44
00:02:45,230 --> 00:02:46,940
defines when various sets of

45
00:02:46,940 --> 00:02:50,665
usable functionality or products will be delivered to the customer.

46
00:02:50,665 --> 00:02:54,210
They discuss critical dates and milestones,

47
00:02:54,210 --> 00:03:00,160
a coordinated with dependent systems and balanced business value versus quality.

48
00:03:00,160 --> 00:03:06,185
Release planning occurs once per release and is time-boxed to 20 minutes.

49
00:03:06,185 --> 00:03:08,464
In the sprint planning ceremony,

50
00:03:08,464 --> 00:03:11,455
work to be performed in the sprint is planned.

51
00:03:11,455 --> 00:03:15,280
The agenda includes creating a sprint backlog,

52
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:17,305
planning out the tasks,

53
00:03:17,305 --> 00:03:19,990
and estimating at the task level.

54
00:03:19,990 --> 00:03:22,570
This can occur a few times per sprint,

55
00:03:22,570 --> 00:03:26,210
but is time-boxed to a total of eight hours per sprint.

56
00:03:26,210 --> 00:03:28,305
In the daily stand ups,

57
00:03:28,305 --> 00:03:33,700
the Agile Team synchronizes activities and creates a plan for the next 24 hours.

58
00:03:33,700 --> 00:03:37,040
Each team member answers three questions.

59
00:03:37,040 --> 00:03:39,630
What did they do since the last time we met?

60
00:03:39,630 --> 00:03:41,865
What do I plan to accomplish today,

61
00:03:41,865 --> 00:03:44,445
and what impediments am I encountering.

62
00:03:44,445 --> 00:03:46,870
The daily stand up is held daily,

63
00:03:46,870 --> 00:03:48,625
preferably in the morning,

64
00:03:48,625 --> 00:03:51,440
and is time-boxed to 15 minutes.

65
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:53,880
In this sprint review and demo,

66
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:55,470
along with the demo,

67
00:03:55,470 --> 00:04:02,140
the Agile Team discusses marketplace changes and the backlog with the PO.

68
00:04:02,140 --> 00:04:05,540
The team presents the completed sprint deliverables to

69
00:04:05,540 --> 00:04:10,370
the product owner based on acceptance criteria and the definition of done.

70
00:04:10,370 --> 00:04:16,110
This occurs once per sprint and is time-boxed to four hours per sprint.

